# MMS Design Specification

> **Internal Document** - Implementation guide for the interactive demo with Vite + React 18 + deck.gl
>
> **Source of Truth**: `docs/RFQ.md` only
>
> **Primary Feature**: Planning View with Sandbox Mode (What-If Scenarios)

---

## 1. Executive Summary

### 1.1 Objective

Win the bidding process by demonstrating an exceptional frontend solution that addresses all client pain points from the RFQ. The demo must visually impress while proving we can deliver a production-ready "Single Pane of Glass" for Rolling Stock Maintenance.

### 1.2 RFQ Pain Points → Our Solutions

| # | Client Pain Point (RFQ) | Our Solution | Key Visual Element |
|---|------------------------|--------------|-------------------|
| 1 | No dedicated mileage management tools | Purpose-built mileage dashboard | KPI Cards + Mileage indicators |
| 2 | IBM Maximo only does asset management | Integrated mileage + maintenance planning | Unified Planning View |
| 3 | Manual Excel management | Interactive visual timeline with drag operations | Gantt-style canvas |
| 4 | Folder-driven data storage | Centralized fleet visualization | Sidebar + Fleet grid |
| 5 | Limited maintenance-operations integration | Single pane for both teams | Shared workspace |
| 6 | Non-compliance risk (underrun/overrun) | Visual alerts + compliance indicators | Color-coded tasks + banners |
| 7 | **No predictive simulations** | **Sandbox Mode for what-if scenarios** | **PRIMARY FEATURE** |
| 8 | Insufficient resource visibility | Resource utilization panels | Heatmap + capacity bars |
| 9 | Manual handling delays | Automated scheduling visualization | Smart conflict detection |

